Can you confirm that the same thing I run locally should be running on AWS? Last night I got response:

> Hello XXX
>
> Your Tunnel Practice 1 simulation with id 15de7ba1-e825-4f39-b8d2-34f427e8416c has finished successfully.  
> Summary
>
> \{  
> "sim\_time\_duration\_avg": 0,  
> "sim\_time\_duration\_std\_dev": 0,  
> "real\_time\_duration\_avg": 0,  
> "real\_time\_duration\_std\_dev": 0,  
> "model\_count\_avg": 0,  
> "model\_count\_std\_dev": 0  
> \}
>
> Regards,
>
> Open Robotics Team

which looks like it was not running at all?? I tried combination of our exploration for 2 minutes \+ subt\_seed artifact report, which worked fine locally, but not on Amazon. Any suggestion what I can check?

In the `server_console.log` logfile I have seen many:

‌

```
(2019-09-20T21:25:36.777638510) Triangle input has a count of zero. This is likely not desired
(2019-09-20T21:25:36.779115512) Triangle input has a count of zero. This is likely not desired
(2019-09-20T21:25:36.780550260) Triangle input has a count of zero. This is likely not desired
(2019-09-20T21:25:36.781976833) Triangle input has a count of zero. This is likely not desired 
```

which I have not seen locally - is it expected?
